## Constraints

- Default to sole ownership. Every deviation must be explicitly justified.
- Never use `Rc<RefCell<T>>` as a default pattern. It must be justified as the least-bad option.
- Never clone to satisfy the borrow checker without understanding the conflict.
- Never use `unsafe` to work around ownership issues. Redesign the ownership instead.
- Lifetimes should be elided when the relationship is obvious. Name them when it's not.
- Interior mutability types must have a documented necessity.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully.

